                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F26 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F26, and at circuit 14F measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F26, 14F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (35) and at circuit 50, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), 50 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 50, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test headlight switch (35) by placing switch in headlight on position, and
                                measuring resistance from term. 1 to 2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(35), term. 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective headlight switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (17) and reconnect connector (35). With headlight switch still
                                on, measure voltage at (17) from circuit 51F to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), 51F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 51F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (17), going to floor- mounted dimmer switch, measure resistance from
                                green wire to blue wire with the switch in dim position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(17), green wire to blue wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (17), going to floor- mounted dimmer switch, measure resistance from
                                green wire to brown wire with the switch in bright position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(17), green wire to brown wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (2) and reconnect (17). With headlight switch still on, move
                                dimmer switch to dim position and at (2), measure voltage from circuit 53 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(2), 53 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (502) and (504) and reconnect (2). With switches still set, at
                                (502), measure voltage from circuit 53B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(502), 53B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53 or 53B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(504), 53A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (502) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53B to
                                11-GC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(502), 53B to 11-GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GC or 11-GB, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (504) with switches still set, measure voltage from circuit 53A to
                                11-GE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(504), 53A to 11-GE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GE or 11-GB, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Move headlight switch to headlight position and dimmer switch to high beam position.
                                Disconnect connector (2) and measure voltage from circuit 52 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(2), 52 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With connectors (502) and (504) still disconnected and switches still set, reconnect
                                conn. (2) and at (502) measure voltage from circuit 52C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(502), 52C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With switches still set, at (504) measure voltage from circuit 52B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(504), 52B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (178) and with headlight switch in headlight position and dimmer
                                switch in dim position, at (178) circuit 66C, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(178), 66C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Move dimmer switch to high beam position and at conn. (178) circuit 66E, measure
                                voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(178), 66E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (165) and reconnect (178). With switches still set, at (165) measure
                                voltage from circuit 66E to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(165), 66E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Move dimmer switch to dim position and at conn. (165) circuit 66C, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(165), 66C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (165) and circuit 66-GA, measure resistance to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(165), 66-GA to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66-GA, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Acc</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Move key switch to accessories position and at conn. (165) circuit 66, measure voltage
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(165), 66 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove fuse F31 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F31.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At fuse F31 and circuit 14L measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>F31, 14L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>24.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At conn. (165) measure voltage from circuit 66A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(165), 66A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>25.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (168) and at circuit 66-G, measure resistance to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(168), 66-G to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66-G, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With parking brake applied, measure resistance across park brake switch (168).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Across switch (168).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective DRL park brake switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (168) and disconnect conn. (28). With park brake applied, at conn.
                                (165) and circuit 66J, measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(165), 66J to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66J or 66K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>28.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (91) and reconnect conn. (165). Move headlight switch to headlight
                                position, and dimmer switch to dim position. At conn. (91) circuit 64A, measure voltage
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(91), 64A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 64A or replace DRL module if circuit checks
